com.analog.lyric.dimple.events

Class DimpleEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.EventObject
      • com.analog.lyric.dimple.events.DimpleEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.analog.lyric.util.misc.IPrintable, java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DataEvent, ModelEvent, SolverEvent

    @ThreadSafe
public abstract class DimpleEvent
extends java.util.EventObject
implements com.analog.lyric.util.misc.IPrintable
    Abstract base class for all Dimple events.

    Concrete subclasses should be immutable and should support serialization. Subclasses must not attempt to serialize the model or solver graphs themselves!

    Since:
    0.06
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • getSource

        @Nullable
public IDimpleEventSource getSource()
        The object that generated this event.

        This should be non-null for a freshly generated event, but will not be preserved by serialization (i.e. it will be null on a deserialized instance).

        Overrides:

      • consumed

        public final boolean consumed()
        Indicate whether event has been "consumed" by a handler and will therefore not be passed on for additional handling.

        This attribute will not be serialized (i.e. will be false when deserialized).

      • getModelId

        public int getModelId()
        The id of the model object associated with the source of the event, if applicable.

        This is the same as the the value of INameable.getId() on getModelObject() when the latter is non-null. This is preserved by serialization.

        Since:
        0.06

      • getSourceName

        public java.lang.String getSourceName()
        The name of the event source.

        Returns value of IDimpleEventSource.getEventSourceName() for source returned by getSource(), but unlike the source itself this value is preserved by serialization.
